+          .ofDefault("hoge")
+          .andThen((registry, log, id) -> {
+              return id.withTags("grpc-status", log.responseTrailers().get("grpc-status"));
+          });
+  ```
+- Both synchronous and asynchronous APIs to select an <type://Endpoint> are added to
+  <type://EndpointSelector> and thus <type://EndpointGroup> which is a sub-interface. #1910 #2837
+  ```java
+  ClientRequestContext ctx = ...
+  EndpointGroup group = ...
+   // synchronous selection!
+  Endpoint endpoint = group.selectNow(ctx);
+   // asynchronous selection!
+  CompletableFuture<Endpoint> future = group.select(ctx, ctx.eventLoop(), 1000 /* timeout */ );
+  ```
+  - Thanks to this change, you can now avoid the <type://EmptyEndpointGroupException> at least
+    for the case where the <typeplural://Endpoint> disappear temporarily.
+- You can now get the snapshot status of circuit breakers from monitoring system. #2841
+- You can now schedule a request timeout in nanoseconds. #2864
+  - <type://ServiceRequestContext#setRequestTimeout(TimeoutMode,Duration)>
+  - <type://ClientRequestContext#setResponseTimeout(TimeoutMode,Duration)>

